<section style="padding: 20px; max-width: 1200px; margin: auto; text-align: left; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">
    <h1>README</h1>
    <h2>News Homepage</h2>
    <p>This project provides the structure and styling for a news homepage, similar to popular news aggregation sites. It includes a responsive design that adapts to various screen sizes, featuring a header with navigation, a main content area with featured articles, and a sidebar for additional widgets.</p>

    <h3>Table of Contents</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><a href="#installation">Installation</a></li>
        <li><a href="#usage">Usage</a></li>
        <li><a href="#file-structure">File Structure</a></li>
        <li><a href="#customization">Customization</a></li>
        <li><a href="#contributing">Contributing</a></li>
        <li><a href="#license">License</a></li>
    </ul>

    <h3 id="installation">Installation</h3>
    <p>To get started with this project, you can clone the repository and open the HTML file in your browser.</p>

    <pre><code>
git clone https://github.com/your-username/news-homepage.git
cd news-homepage
    </code></pre>

    <p>Open <code>index.html</code> in your preferred web browser to view the homepage.</p>

    <h3 id="usage">Usage</h3>
    <p>The main HTML file (<code>index.html</code>) contains the structure of the homepage. The CSS styles are embedded within the HTML file for simplicity, but they can be separated into an external stylesheet if desired.</p>

    <h4>Key Components</h4>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Header:</strong> Includes the logo, search bar, and menu icon.</li>
        <li><strong>Navigation:</strong> Contains navigation links for different sections of the site.</li>
        <li><strong>Main Content:</strong> Features a grid layout with featured articles and additional articles.</li>
        <li><strong>Sidebar:</strong> Contains widgets for top stories and watchlist movers.</li>
        <li><strong>Footer:</strong> Basic footer with copyright information.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>HTML Structure</h4>
    <pre><code>
&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html lang="en"&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
    &lt;meta charset="UTF-8"&gt;
    &lt;meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"&gt;
    &lt;title&gt;News Homepage&lt;/title&gt;
    &lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0-beta3/css/all.min.css"&gt;
    &lt;style&gt;
        /* CSS styles here */
    &lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
    &lt;!-- Header Section --&gt;
    &lt;div class="header"&gt;
        &lt;div class="menu-icon"&gt;&lt;i class="fas fa-bars"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class="search-bar"&gt;&lt;input type="text" placeholder="Search"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class="logo"&gt;&lt;h1&gt;Blog Logo&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;!-- Navigation Section --&gt;
    &lt;div class="nav"&gt;
        &lt;a href="#"&gt;Work feed&lt;/a&gt;
        &lt;a href="#"&gt;Discover&lt;/a&gt;
        &lt;!-- More links --&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;!-- Main Content Area --&gt;
    &lt;div class="container"&gt;
        &lt;div class="main-content"&gt;
            &lt;!-- Featured Articles --&gt;
            &lt;div class="featured"&gt;
                &lt;img src="https://example.com/featured-image.jpg" alt="Featured"&gt;
                &lt;div class="content"&gt;
                    &lt;h2 class="title"&gt;Featured Article Title&lt;/h2&gt;
                    &lt;p class="text"&gt;Description of the featured article...&lt;/p&gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;!-- Additional Articles --&gt;
            &lt;div class="article"&gt;
                &lt;img src="https://example.com/article1.jpg" alt="Article"&gt;
                &lt;div class="content"&gt;
                    &lt;h3 class="title"&gt;Article Title&lt;/h3&gt;
                    &lt;p class="text"&gt;Brief description of the article...&lt;/p&gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class="sidebar"&gt;
            &lt;!-- Widgets --&gt;
            &lt;div class="widget"&gt;
                &lt;h3&gt;Top stories&lt;/h3&gt;
                &lt;p&gt;Breaking news and updates...&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;div class="widget"&gt;
                &lt;h3&gt;Watchlist movers&lt;/h3&gt;
                &lt;p&gt;Stock data...&lt;/p&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;!-- Footer Section --&gt;
    &lt;div class="footer"&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;&amp;copy; 2024 Blog. All rights reserved.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
    </code></pre>

    <h3 id="customization">Customization</h3>
    <p>To customize the layout and design, you can modify the HTML structure and CSS styles. For instance, you can change the colors, fonts, and layout by editing the respective CSS properties.</p>

    <h4>Example Customization</h4>
    <p>To change the background color of the header, you can modify the <code>.header</code> class in the CSS:</p>
    <pre><code>
.header {
    background-color: #0044cc; /* New background color */
    /* Other styles */
}
    </code></pre>

    <h3 id="contributing">Contributing</h3>
    <p>Contributions are welcome! If you have suggestions for improvements or new features, feel free to create an issue or submit a pull request.</p>

    <ol>
        <li>Fork the repository.</li>
        <li>Create a new branch (<code>git checkout -b feature-branch</code>).</li>
        <li>Make your changes.</li>
        <li>Commit your changes (<code>git commit -am 'Add new feature'</code>).</li>
        <li>Push to the branch (<code>git push origin feature-branch</code>).</li>
        <li>Create a new Pull Request.</li>
    </ol>

